other_tests.procedure_name: ERCP with sphincterotomy and spyglass cholangioscopy
other_tests.findings: Filling defects noted in the gallbladder neck; scope could not traverse a valve, not amenable to therapy.

Mild bibasilar dependent atelectasis; normal liver contour and no focal hepatic lesions; mild fat stranding adjacent to the gallbladder fossa; unremarkable visualized portions of the pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and bowel; no hydronephrosis, free air, or lymphadenopathy.
